kernel_variant.question:
Let

S^{3}=\{(x_{1},x_{2},x_{3},x_{4})\in\mathbb R^{4}:x_{1}^{2}+x_{2}^{2}+x_{3}^{2}+x_{4}^{2}=1\}

be the unit 3-sphere.  Prove that among any nine points on S^{3} there exist six that lie in one closed hemisphere of S^{3}; that is, in a set of the form

H(v)=\{x\in S^{3}:\langle x,v\rangle\ge 0\}

for some non-zero vector v\in\mathbb R^{4}.
